The NIST Trusted Identities Group (TIG) works with its partners to drive trust, convenience, and innovation in the marketplace of identity solutions by promoting government and commercial adoption of privacy enhancing, secure, interoperable, and easy-to-use digital solutions. Established in 2015, the TIGâ€™s goal is to convene, facilitate, and catalyze a private sector-led implementation approach to advancing trusted digital identity solutions and to enable government adoption by continually evolving the risk-based federal guidance to encourage the adoption of innovative technologies in the market. 

